when a new site is created
create a directory to house images. keep in mind the future use of site dir stores
when a user inserts an image to the publication using ![image name](images/image-name.png) the image must be
retrieved from the sites dir and not a global directory

we may have to use outputstream to get images since am not sure if dirs will be accessible

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2692772/how-can-i-create-a-new-folder-in-my-web-app-for-upload-photo-album-with-grails

define root path in webapp using groovy.config
set inside of rootpath the sitename+date as dir
when site created save images from reports to this root path
call images from this root path to display
set permissions correctly as read/write by app main user or site users kerberos auth via service

